o need to ensure the persistence.xml includes all necessary classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering entity associations**\\n\\nI'm exploring how to handle entity associations. I can use session.fetch(article.getAuthor()), especially if getAuthor returns a proxy with @ManyToOne(fetch=LAZY). This setup should queue the batch properly. The batch loader would then initialize all queued lazy entity associations when resolving the first author. I need to ensure that the BatchAuthor entity has the @BatchSize. The batch fetch size on the target entity or default hibernate.default_batch_fetch_size is something to keep in mind too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_g6XWwKqBZjPe5IQ6WNcyU4l6|fc_04a8a56e44fb2ef1016a15e328d6f481a18c44e608a329aec1", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hibernate.reactive/hibernate-reactive-core/2.0.7.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate_reactive/hibernate_reactive_core/entity/Author.java"}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_0Xkwk1IkgOTGIKPhKh7lhFLD|fc_04a8a56e44fb2ef1016a15e328d70881a183880c6c8f41c482", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hibernate.reactive/hibernate-reactive-core/2.0.7.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate_reactive/hibernate_reactive_core/entity/Book.java"}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NzQwb5TKkU1rMAc2awbgWi77|fc_04a8a56e44fb2ef1016a15e328d71081a1ae29d5790de978ef", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hibernate.reactive/hibernate-reactive-core/2.0.7.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate_reactive/hibernate_reactive_core/entity/BatchDepartment.java"}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Gje3PU3jN0kUODY0KXj3nndf|fc_04a8a56e44fb2ef1016a15e328d71881a1ab80446c5ccb1484", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hibernate.reactive/hibernate-reactive-core/2.0.7.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate_reactive/hibernate_reactive_core/entity/BatchEmployee.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 270, "output": 1246, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38892, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779819285434, "responseId": "resp_04a8a56e44fb2ef1016a15e316d55c81a1a0a23026330f3fa8"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_g6XWwKqBZjPe5IQ6WNcyU4l6|fc_04a8a56e44fb2ef1016a15e328d6f481a18c44e608a329aec1", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_hibernate_reactive.hibernate_reactive_core.entity;\n\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport jakarta.persistence.Entity;\nimport jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\nimport jakarta.persistence.Id;\nimport jakarta.persistence.OneToMany;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\n\nimport static jakarta.persistence.CascadeType.PERSIST;\n\n@Entity\npublic class Author {\n    @Id\n    @GeneratedValue\n    private Integer id;\n\n    @NotNull\n    @Size(max = 100)\n    private String name;\n\n    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"author\", cascade = PERSIST)\n    private List<Book> books = new ArrayList<>();\n\n    public Author() {\n    }\n\n    public Author(String name) {\n        this.name = name;\n    }\n\n    public Integer getId() {\n        return id;\n    }\n\n    public String getName() {\n        return name;\n    }\n\n    public List<Book> getBooks() {\n        return books;\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1779819305282}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_0Xkwk1IkgOTGIKPhKh7lhFLD|fc_04a8a56e44fb2ef1016a15e328d70881a183880c6c8f41c482", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 le