e is still in the worktree, any failure here could be problematic. Adding a PU for the collection doesn’t change behavior but does reference pre-existing untracked items. I need to check the build.gradle for the org.postgresql version and ensure there’s no hardcoding of artifact versions in test inputs, as the user advised against it. Choosing version 42.7 might be an option.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining process behavior**\\n\\nI’m considering using a timeout that waits up to five seconds and returns false without destroying anything. That might not be ideal, but it’s good to have some bounds. I’ll need to address potential issues if the Postgres container fails to start due to an image being missing. It seems like I might also need to inspect how Gradle runs the current working directory. Maybe I should look at updating the metadata-user-code-filter too? Let’s dig into that.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5q8hX5fEoOckEJGjX4gM9qff|fc_04a8a56e44fb2ef1016a15e3d8fed081a19d10e9902f67ee90", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hibernate.reactive/hibernate-reactive-core/2.0.7.Final/metadata-user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1015, "output": 912, "cacheRead": 55808, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57735, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779819463509, "responseId": "resp_04a8a56e44fb2ef1016a15e3c82c1481a1b4412215e16c8ca8"}}
